    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Madison, Inda.</placeName>
                <date>20 March 1863</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Phila</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Revd and Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Enclosed I forward you certain<lb/> resolutions passed by my
                congregation. I do not ask you<lb/> to copy them, for I know your principles too
                well, but<lb/> I do entreat you (for my sake) to make some little<lb/> not thereof
                in your <hi rend="underline">News</hi> columns, for none of my<lb/> friends in
                    <placeName>England</placeName> or <placeName>Jamaica</placeName> see any other
                than<lb/> your periodical. I have to entreat at same time<lb/> to send me Three
                Copies <add>דרך האמונה</add> each enveloped and sent<lb/> by Post (postage 4 cts)
                and would feel obliged at same<lb/> time by an early reply to my last
                communication.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">With sincere regards believe me</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Truly Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">A. J. H Bernal</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
